  "title": "Events & Content Design Support",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will coordinate with internal and external partners to execute department events and activities, create and distribute video and communication materials, and handle administrative and operational tasks to support the department’s goals.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Coordinate with internal teams and external partners to plan and execute company events such as Townhalls, workplan retreats, and staff engagement activities</li><li>Create and edit videos and design internal communication materials including Electronic Direct Mail (EDM) and presentation slides to support department initiatives</li><li>Distribute communication materials to relevant stakeholders in a timely manner</li><li>Manage administrative and operational tasks to ensure smooth department functioning</li><li>Collaborate effectively within the department and with external partners to meet project deadlines and quality standards</li><li>Maintain organized records and documentation related to events and communications</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in video editing and graphic design to produce engaging internal communication content</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications (Word, Excel) to prepare documents and reports</li><li>Strong analytical skills to assess communication needs and improve materials</li><li>Effective communication skills to liaise with partners and team members clearly</li><li>Attention to detail and organizational skills to manage multiple tasks accurately</li><li>Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment and with external stakeholders</li><li>Demonstrate integrity and a commitment to delivering high-quality work</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Salary: $2650/month</li><li>Working Arrangement: Mon-Fri</li><li>Working Location: Buona Vista</li><li>Contract Period: 6 months</li></ul><p>EA License No: 96C4864<br />Reg. No.: R24121728 EUNICE WOO JING QI</p>",
